                <p>
                    Imagine a check. If you wanted to pay your best friend, Skyler, $100, how would you do it? You would first start out by giving him a check for $100. He would then deposit that check into his bank account. Your bank now owes your best friend $100 more and you $100 less. This is how current payment systems work. They are all based on debt.
