                <h3> Ripple FAQ  </h3>

                <p> <b> Q </b>: How many Ripples will be released? </p>

                <p> <b> A </b>: 100 billion Ripples are planned to be released. The company will keep half of them with themselves.</p>

                <p> <b> Q</b>: Who is building Ripple? </p>

                <p> <b> A</b>: OpenCoin is building Ripple. It was co-founded by Chris Larsen (CEO) and Jed McCaleb (CTO).  </p>

                <p> <b> Q</b>: What are some of the criticisms of Ripple? </p>

                <p> <b> A</b>: 1. When Ripple began, the company created 100 billion XRP out of nowhere with the creators retaining 20% of the supply. <br>
                               2. Ripple currently owns over 60% of the supply of all XRP <br>
                               3. Relatively closed system. You cannot just download a wallet. Ripple controls the servers that allow transactions. <br>
                               4. Centralized. They are no miners. The blockchain is operated by one entity. </p>

